rules_version = '2';

/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   CLARK Factory — Firebase Storage Rules
   V21.9.98 EMERGENCY DIAGNOSTIC — MAX PERMISSIVE
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Ahmed reports ALL storage uploads failing with storage/unauthorized:
     - templates/** (campaign images)  — FAIL
     - orders/**/attachments/** (order attachments) — FAIL
     - documents/** (new Documents Tree) — FAIL

   Tests A/B/C in earlier session diagnostic PASSED (text + image to
   templates/_diag_*/). But real production uploads FAIL. The V21.9.97
   max-permissive documents/** also failed.

   This points to the rules NOT being the root cause. Most likely:
   1. App Check enforcement in Firebase Console (Storage tab)
   2. Rules deploy is broken — live rules don't match repo
   3. Auth token not being sent on writes (but reads work?)

   V21.9.98 STRATEGY: bypass all role/MIME/size checks. Allow any
   authed user to do everything. If THIS still fails → confirmed the
   issue is upstream of rules. If it works → at least one of the
   helpers (hasRole/isWriteSafe/isAllowedMime) is broken globally.

   ⚠️ THIS IS TEMPORARY. Once we identify the cause, restore proper
   security via storage.rules.SECURE.bak (see at end of file).
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

service firebase.storage {
  match /b/{bucket}/o {

    /* Auth-only — any authed user can do anything anywhere.
       Deny only happens for unauthenticated requests. */
    match /{allPaths=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null;
    }

  }
}
